=== Big Omega notation ===

Another asymptotic notation is formula_121, read &quot;big omega&quot;. There are two widespread and incompatible definitions of the statement

:formula_122 as formula_123,

where &quot;a&quot; is some real number, formula_124, or formula_125, where &quot;f&quot; and &quot;g&quot; are real functions defined in a neighbourhood of &quot;a&quot;, and where &quot;g&quot; is positive in this neighbourhood.

The Hardy–Littlewood definition is used mainly in analytic number theory, and the Knuth definition mainly in computational complexity theory; the definitions are not equivalent.

