==== The Knuth definition ====
In 1976 Donald Knuth published a paper to justify his use of the formula_121-symbol to describe a stronger property. Knuth wrote: &quot;For all the applications I have seen so far in computer science, a stronger requirement ... is much more appropriate&quot;. He defined

:formula_159

with the comment: &quot;Although I have changed Hardy and Littlewood&#x27;s definition of formula_121, I feel justified in doing so because their definition is by no means in wide use, and because there are other ways to say what they want to say in the comparatively rare cases when their definition applies.&quot;

=== Family of Bachmann–Landau notations ===
{g(n)} &lt; \infty&lt;/math&gt;
